Mary Doyle vs. Frank O’Farrell. At special term, August, 1866. 2?. Brown, for the defendant. O. A. Some, for the plaintiff. Decided August 15, 1866.

Before Robertson, Ch. J.

Delays in bringing on the trial of issues, caused by frequent promises of the defendant to settle, are not a good ground for dismissing the complaint for want of prosecution.
